nodes.text: Vine snakes were venomous serpents found in jungle regions of planets such as Kashyyyk, Dagobah, and Wayland.
They would lie in wait on branches, or among vines for camouflage, waiting for prey to pass underneath. They then dropped down and killed their victims through gradual constriction.
Vine snakes made up several breeds. Some were thick with brown scales and black mottling. A smaller breed was thin and black with yellow striped patterns.
